Seminar on DPRK's Joint New Year Editorial Held in Democratic Congo 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, January 12 (KCNA) -- The Group for the Study of Kim Jong Il's Juche Idea and the Youth Group for the Study of the Juche Idea in Democratic Congo held a joint seminar on the joint New Year editorial published in the
DPRK on Jan. 5.
 Nzemba Yangana, chairman of the youth group, and other speakers said that the shining victory and achievements made by the army and people of the DPRK last year are the brilliant fruition of Kim Jong Il's absolute leadership prestige and ever-victorious political ability. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They expressed belief that the tasks of the Korean people to greet the 60th anniversaries of the Workers' Party of Korea and the liberation of the country as great festivals of victors would be successfully carried out under the banner of the great Juche idea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 All the Korean people will effect a great turn in accomplishing the cause of reunification under the uplifted banner of cooperation for national independence, cooperation for peace against war and cooperation for reunification and patriotism and thus brilliantly decorate this year which marks the 5th anniversary of the June 15 North-South Joint Declaration, they stressed.

Joint New Year Editorial Studied Abroad 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, January 12 (KCNA) -- A seminar on the joint New Year editorial of the newspapers of the Workers' Party, the army and the youth league of
the DPRK was held by the Ukraine Association for the Study of Songun Policy on Jan. 5.
 Grigori Shubed, chairman of the association, said that achievements made by the Korean people last year are entirely ascribable to the Songun revolutionary leadership of Kim Jong Il, stressing they would emerge victorious despite the U.S. imperialists' vicious moves to isolate and stifle the DPRK as long as they are united close around him.
 Similar seminars were held by the Ukrainian Society for the Study of the Juche Idea and the Ukraine-DPRK Friendship Association on the same day. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 That day the Indian Youth Group for the Study of Works of Comrade Kim Il Sung held a reading session on the joint editorial. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Chairman of the group Balzor Singh Chauhan read the part of the editorial dealing with Korea's reunification. He expressed the hope that all the Koreans would realize the three forms of cooperation--cooperation for national independence, cooperation for peace against war and cooperation for reunification and patriotism--in the idea of "By our nation itself" and thus achieve great success in their movement for national reunification this significant year which marks the 60th anniversary of the liberation of
Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. is the primary target of the Korean people in their struggle for reunification, he noted, demanding it drop the plan to stifle the DPRK and its hostile policy toward the latter.

Chinese Technicians Resolved to Display Sino-Korean Friendship 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, January 12 (KCNA) -- The members of the Chinese technical delegation participating in the construction of the Taean Friendship Glass Factory which is taking shape as a symbol of DPRK-China friendship are full of enthusiasm to help toward the development of the friendly relations between the two countries by wrapping up the construction ahead of schedule. 
 Head of the delegation Chui Baoyu said he heartily felt the pride of taking part in the construction of the factory now underway amid the deep concern of respected Hu Jintao and leader Kim Jong Il, expressing the determination to make energetic efforts to build the factory as an edifice of eternal value which might compare favorably with best ones in the distant future by pooling strength with builders of the DPRK so as to live up to the expectation of the leaders and peoples of the two countries. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Member of the delegation Li Fuqiang said he was deeply impressed by the strivings of soldiers of the Korean People's Army effecting innovations in the construction, stressing that the KPA which takes upon itself both national defense and socialist construction is a true army of the people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The construction of the factory, he added, will be a momentous occasion in deepening friendship between the two peoples which has been developing through centuries. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Member of the delegation Wang Zhiliang stated that the factory would be built in grand style, backed by the friendship and fraternity and warm hearts of the peoples and builders of the two countries to demonstrate to the world the invincibility of Sino-Korean friendship.

Rodong Sinmun Urges Cooperation for Reunification and Patriotism 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, January 12 (KCNA) -- Cooperation for reunification and patriotism is a vital requisite to the accomplishment of the cause of national reunification and a sure guarantee for its victory, declares Rodong Sinmun today in a signed article.
 It goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Given this cooperation, national independence and reunification, common prosperity and interests of the nation could be achieved, but, without it, the Koreans would undergo as ever the misfortune and agony of division. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Cooperation for reunification and patriotism is a powerful weapon which helps strengthen the driving force of reunification and frustrate the interference of outside forces in the affair of reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Hating reconciliation and unity of the Korean nation, the U.S. pursues a crafty national estrangement policy to curb it. It seeks in this to bar the Koreans from possessing a powerful weapon in the form of unity. If all the fellow countrymen aspiring after reunification got united and cooperated with each other, there would be no impasse unsolvable and no fortress unconquerable in settling the reunification issue. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Cooperation for reunification and patriotism is a driving force which makes it possible to promote the reunification movement triumphantly through trials and difficulties of all descriptions. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The "security" of south Korea also can be ensured by embodying the patriotic idea of "By our nation itself" and its economic stability can be guaranteed by this cooperation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Cooperation for reunification and patriotism is a mighty force to defend the sovereignty of the country and the dignity of the nation and "cooperation" with outsiders is treacherous "cooperation" bringing subordination, confrontation and division. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
The more the situation within and without gets complicated and the more blatant the anti-reunification divisive forces become in their maneuvers, the closer the reunification forces supporting the June 15 joint declaration and wanting its implementation should get united to pave a wide avenue of independent reunification, breaking through the trials and difficulties with the might of unity.

Joint Meeting with Korean Schoolchildren from Japan
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, January 12 (KCNA) -- A joint meeting was held at the People's Palace of Culture on Tuesday between schoolchildren of Pyongyang and members of the art group of Korean schoolchildren from Japan led by Kim Jong Song.
 The principal of Samhung Middle School and other speakers at the meeting noted that the dance tale "Strength of Love" and other numbers that the group put on the stage of the New Year performance touched the right chord in the hearts of the audience and delighted the people and schoolchildren of the homeland. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They said the schoolchildren of the motherland firmly believe that the members of the group would give steady continuity to patriotism. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The head and members of the group spoke of the love shown by leader Kim Jong Il to them and expressed the resolution of the schoolchildren in Japan to grow up as reliable personnel to shoulder the movement of Koreans in Japan. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The participants gave a joint performance.

Three-point Cooperation for National Reunification
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, January 12 (KCNA) -- The joint New Year editorial sets forth the slogan "Let's advance under the banner of cooperation for national independence, peace against war, and patriotism for reunification!"
 This slogan reflects the June 15 joint declaration, which solemnly declared at home and abroad the will of the Korean nation to solve the issue of the country's reunification independently by its concerted efforts. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Now a grave situation has been created on the Korean peninsula by the internal and external separatists' obstructions. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. is blocking the improvement of the north-south relations and obstructing the independent reunification of the nation, forcing the south Korean authorities to pursue the policy toward the north under its control. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Chiming with the United States' anti-reunification moves, the south Korean ultra-right conservatives have aggravated the inter-Korean relations with reckless confrontation with the north. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Pak Kyong Chol, vice department director of the Secretariat of the Committee for the Peaceful Reunification of the Fatherland, told KCNA that the present situation urges the Koreans to strengthen the three-point cooperation--national independence, peace against war and patriotism for reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 All the fellow countrymen should, with the consciousness of national independence, root out flunkeyism, reject foreign interference in the efforts for the country's reunification and realize cooperation for national independence, he said, and continued:
 What is the main point in the cooperation for peace against war is the anti-U.S. struggle. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Ringing out are voices calling for putting an end to the U.S. military presence in south Korea through a nation-wide struggle for peace against war under the slogans "Let us no longer allow the nearly-60-year-long U.S. occupation" and "Let our nation live together without the U.S." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  The reunification of the country is the highest expression of patriotism for the nation.
  Those, with the spirit and same blood of the nation, should join the patriotic struggle for reunification and render a tangible contribution to the cause. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  The Korean nation should make positive efforts for the three-point cooperation, which will open a new phase for its reunification under the idea of "By our nation itself."

Students Enjoy Winter Vacation
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, January 12 (KCNA) -- Students are enjoying their winter vacation in the Democratic People's Republic of Korea.
 There are one hundred and scores of schoolchildren's palaces, youth halls and children's halls across the country. Every day a lot of school youth and children visit them where they are acquiring general knowledge of basic sciences and are cultivating sports, dance, music, fine art talents according to their tastes. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the Grand People's Study House and schoolchildren's palaces in different parts of the country, many students are engrossed in studying computer technology with an ambition to become standard-bearers in the era of IT industry. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Students, sensitive to new things and strong in enterprising spirit, frequently gather to express what they learned in books and films. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The school youth league and children's union organizations organize colorful activities including visit to revolutionary battle and historic sites, museums and exhibition halls and get-togethers with heroes to firmly equip them with the revolutionary traditions of the Workers' Party of Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 University students visit rural communities and industrial establishments to give art performances, thus greatly inspiring working people in their efforts for implementing tasks set forth in the joint New Year editorial. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Squares, playgrounds, rivers and lakes are animated with children enjoying skating, sledging and top spinning and playing folk amusement and sports games.

Kim Jong Il Gives Field Guidance to Pukjung Machine Complex
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, January 12 (KCNA) -- Kim Jong Il, general secretary of the Workers' Party of Korea and chairman of the DPRK National Defence Commission, visited the Pukjung Machine Complex and encouraged the workers in their production drive for the new year.
 He was accompanied by Kim Phyong Hae, chief secretary of the North Phyongan Provincial Committee of the WPK, Jon Pyong Ho, secretary of the Central Committee of the WPK, and Ri Yong Chol and Ju Kyu Chang, first vice-department directors of its Central Committee. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Going round the heat treatment shop, the casting shop, the processing shop and other production processes which have undergone changes beyond recognition, he encouraged the workers there who were working spectacular miracles in their drive from the outset of the year to greet the 60th anniversaries of the Party founding and the liberation of the country as the greatest festivals of proud victors in the history of the Party and the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 After acquainting himself in detail with the modernization and production performance at the complex, he set forth tasks to be fulfilled by the complex, noting that it plays an important role in the development of the nation's shipbuilding industry. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In order to develop fisheries and marine transport in the country sea-bound on three sides it is necessary to produce more efficient engines needed for modern fishing boats and cargo ships, he noted. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He underscored the need to steadily push ahead with the work to put the complex on a modern and scientific basis and, at the same time, briskly introduce new technology in order to increase the production of modern machines. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Noting that the economic development, the increase of the defense capability and the improvement of the people's living standard are guaranteed by science and technology, he called for energetically pushing forward the technological updating of national economy on the basis of modern science and technology, true to the WPK's policy of attaching importance to science. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is important to thoroughly establish Juche in putting the production processes on a modern and scientific basis, he said, adding that to this end it is necessary to carry out the technological updating of the complex in a manner favorable for its operation in keeping with its actual conditions. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He called on the officials of the complex to manage and operate it on the basis of a scientific management and business strategy to firmly adhere to the principle of profitability in production. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Saying that the officials, workers and technicians of the complex have a strong resolution, a high ambition and fervent enthusiasm, he underscored the need for its party organization to organize the work to implement the Party policy and actively galvanize the masses into action through a political work in order to realize them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He expressed the expectation and conviction that the workers of Pukjung would creditably perform their mission and role as standard-bearers and a shock force in carrying through the Party's economic policy.
